description: Retail inflation declined in March to a five-month low, driven by lower food inflation. Industrial output growth peaked in February. Data revealed rural and urban inflation, food index, and pulses prices, with potential heatwave and monsoon impacts on food prices.
title: Retail inflation at 5-month low, IIP hits 4-month high

description: Tesla is not the only agenda when Elon Musk meets PM Narendra Modi, but figuring prominently in talks will be Starlink, the satellite communications business of his space company SpaceX. Musk's satellite internet venture has been trying for more than three years to get a licence in India, but has failed to pass govt scrutiny.
title: Beyond Tesla: Elon Musk, PM Modi to take up Starlink too

description: Biden warns Iran against attacking Israel, confirms Tehran's imminent threat. White House vows to defend Israel amid escalating tensions.
title: Biden says expects Iran to attack Israel soon, warns: 'Don't'

description: A 12-year-old mentally challenged boy, missing from Worli, was found using a QR code in Colaba. Police contacted family, verified details, and reunited him. He is part of projectchetna.in.
title: QR code locket helps special child reunite with family

description: Rahul Gandhi criticizes BJP for attacking the Constitution, warning against potential changes in 2024. He stresses the Constitution's role in protecting Indian people's rights and culture, alongside highlighting the significance of INDIA bloc in defending democracy.
title: Constitution, soul of nation, under BJP-RSS attack: Rahul Gandhi

description: PM Modi refutes opposition accusations, emphasizing the Constitution's sanctity and criticizing Congress for alleged subversion. Modi highlights the Constitution's irrevocability, defending it against misuse by the INDIA bloc and questioning calls for nuclear disarmament.
title: Constitution is Gita, Bible & Quran for our government: Modi

description: National Medical Commission (NMC) has clarified that it is yet to grant permission to open new medical colleges for the academic session 2024-25. "Applications received for this academic year are still under process," said a senior official.
title: Medical college applications for 2024-25 still under process: NMC

description: Delhi University leads in CUET-UG 2024 applications, followed by various universities with substantial numbers. According to a study of trend of applications for Common University Entrance Test-Undergraduate (CUET-UG) 2024, Delhi University (DU) is most popular university among 261 participating higher education institutions (HEIs) for undergraduate education. This is however less than last year's 28.3 lakh.
title: With 26 lakh applications, Delhi University leads CUET-UG 2024 race

description: HAL received an RFP for 97 Tejas Mark-1A fighters. The Defence Acquisitions Council approved the acquisition of 'improved' Tejas jets and an upgrade programme for Sukhoi-30MKI jets, along with 156 Prachand choppers.
title: Defence ministry issues tender to HAL for 97 Tejas jets

description: Kashmiri migrant voters in Jammu and Udhampur exempt from 'Form M'. EC allows self-attestation. Special polling stations mapped. Decision after J&K CEO's comments. Polling in phases, vote counting on June 4.
title: EC tweaks rule, makes it easier for Kashmiri migrants to vote

description: IAF conducts night landing in Leh to evacuate soldier with severed hand to Delhi for re-implantation surgery after Ladakh incident. Surgeons stabilize him, prompting advanced treatment and C-130J Hercules airlift within 8-hour window.
title: IAF rescues injured jawan in 'dark night airlift' from Leh

description: Making light of PM Narendra Modi's accusation that opposition leaders are eating non-veg food during auspicious period, Congress on Friday said it does not track the nutrition of political leaders on a monthly basis like he does, but is focused on tracking the growing malnutrition among children under Modi's watch, which is among the worst in the world.
title: Congress takes 'malnutrition' dig at PM after non-veg remark

description: Gopi Thotakura, the trailblazing Indian space tourist, ventures with Blue Origin's New Shephard-25 mission. Co-founding Preserve Life Corp, he champions holistic wellness and applied health worldwide. Born in Vijayawada, Gopi, an entrepreneur and a pilot, will make a journey beyond the Earth's atmosphere with five other candidates. The launch date of the space flight will be announced soon.
title: Andhra-born pilot set to be first Indian to fly to space as tourist

description: Mounting a sharp attack on Congress over its handling of the Kashmir issue, Union home minister Amit Shah on Friday said the party "pampered" Article 370 like an "illegitimate child in its lap for 70 years".  Shah slammed Congress president Mallikarjun Kharge for criticising PM Modi for talking about Kashmir while addressing rallies in other states.
title: For 70 years, Cong pampered Art 370 like illegitimate child: Shah

description: Robusta coffee prices reach unprecedented heights at Rs 10,080 per 50 kg bag. Small growers benefit, while challenges like labour shortage and wildlife threats persist in major coffee-producing regions like Kodagu, Chikkamagaluru, and Hassan.
title: Windfall for Indian growers as robusta output falls elsewhere
PDS scam exceeds Rs 10k crore, money taken to Dubai: ED

description: Students and staff from a private school were quick to respond at an accident site, rescuing injured children from an overturned school bus en route to GL Public School. The school community's swift actions helped save lives and ensure timely medical attention.
title: NCR bus crash: Staff, students of nearby school helped victims

description: The Lancet calls for govt transparency in data sharing for improved health indices in India. Census delay, lack of health survey data, and potential underestimation of Covid-19 deaths are highlighted issues.
title: Lancet: Health data in India has problems

description: ED attaches Rs 230 crore properties in West Bengal teacher recruitment scam, involving Sinha and Roy. Land in Patharghata, Sultanpur, Maheshtala seized. Money laundering probe includes shell entities.
title: ED attaches ₹230cr assets in Bengal teacher job scam

description: AAP ministers and other functionaries on Friday addressed separate press conferences to voice their apprehension that the Centre was laying the ground in Delhi for imposing President's Rule. Minister Atishi alleged that a "big political conspiracy" had been hatched by the BJP-led govt to move in that direction. She warned that any such move would be "illegal, unconstitutional".
title: Centre laying ground to impose President's Rule in Delhi, says Atishi

description: S Nirmala from Pedda Harivanam, Kurnool district, Andhra Pradesh, tops first year intermediate board exams with 95.7%. Despite parents' child marriage plans, she aims to be an IPS officer, advocating against child marriages, empowering girls' dreams.
title: After narrowly escaping child marriage, girl tops SSC exam

description: India appreciates Taliban's positive step in restoring property rights for Afghan Hindus and Sikhs. Taliban authorities were reported to be working to restore private land to Hindu and Sikh minorities, reclaiming these properties from those linked to the previous West-backed regime. Taliban's initiative is seen as a significant step toward redressing the injustices faced by religious minorities in the country
title: India hails Taliban's move to restore property rights of Hindus, Sikhs

description: Arrest of blast suspects in Digha fuels political feud over terrorism in Bengal. Accusations between parties highlight security concerns, with NIA and Bengal police involved in the joint operation.
title: Bengaluru blast accused arrest in Bengal sparks BJP-TMC clash

description: NIA-led multi-agency operation spanning 42 days, the absconding alleged mastermind and executor of the March 1 blast at Bengaluru's Rameswaram Cafe were arrested from their hideout in Bengal's New Digha on Friday. After being alerted that the two were in a lodge in New Digha under assumed identities, NIA requested Bengal police to secure them.
title: Bengaluru cafe blast 'mastermind' and 'bomber' held in Bengal

description: Left-arm spinner Kuldeep Yadav, returning to the side after missing three matches due to a groin injury, claimed three wickets while conceding just 20 runs, keeping the opposition batsmen at bay without conceding any boundaries in his four-over spell. The returning Kuldeep was named Man of the Match for his outstanding bowling performance.
title: Kuldeep credits this person for getting him match ready

description: Indian nationals advised against travel to Iran and Israel. US warns of major retaliatory strike by Iran on Israeli soil. Iran vows revenge for killing of 7 military commanders. Departure of Indian workers halted.
title: Avoid travel to Iran, Israel: Government amid West Asia tension

description: Modi criticized Congress for cooking meat during Hindu periods to appease vote banks. He mentioned Lalu Prasad and Tejashwi, emphasizing people's right to eat anything but questioning the intent behind such actions. Responding to the charge that BJP has exploited Ram Mandir for its electoral advantage, Modi said that the boot, in fact, was on the other foot.
title: PM Modi: Flaunting meat videos in Sawan shows Mughal mindset

description: Debutant Jake Fraser-McGurk, who celebrated his 22nd birthday just the day before, showcased his talent by forming a crucial 77-run partnership for the third wicket with captain Rishabh Pant, who contributed with a solid 41 runs. Their partnership played a pivotal role in DC successfully chasing down LSG's total of 167 runs with 11 balls to spare. With this victory, DC climbed to ninth place in the 10-team IPL standings, marking only their second win in six outings and reigniting their hopes in the competitive T20 tourney.
title: 'Told boys we need to think like...', says Rishabh Pant

description: Despite Lucknow Super Giants posting a competitive total of 167 runs, Delhi Capitals chased down the target with ease in 18.1 overs, losing only four wickets in the process. Jake Frazer-McGurk played a crucial role in the chase, smashing a quick-fire 55 runs off just 35 balls on his IPL debut. He formed a significant partnership with Rishabh Pant, contributing to Delhi Capitals' successful run chase.LSG skipper KL Rahul acknowledged the absence of Mayank and the impact it had on the team's performance, indicating that he may need more time to recover fully before returning to action.
title: Mayank Yadav may miss a couple of more games: KL Rahul

description: The US foreign-born population grew by 15.6 per cent to 46.2 million by 2022, reflecting the nation's immigrant heritage. Nothing signifies the adage that America is a nation of immigrants that the statistics of 1970 where the foreign-born population stood at 9.6 million or just 4.7 per cent of the US population.
title: US has 46.2 million foreign-born, majority of whom are its citizens

description: Australian cricketer Jake Fraser-McGurk announced himself with a belligerent half-century (55 off 35 balls). The 22-year-old, known for his aggressive batting style, made an immediate impact in the IPL by smashing a short of a length delivery from Yash Thakur over deep mid-wicket, securing his first-ever runs in the tournament. Displaying his attacking mindset, he followed up with another six in the subsequent over, showcasing his ability to take on the bowlers and score quickly.
title: 'Amazing time to come to India': Fraser-McGurk

description: Delhi Capitals returned to winning form with a convincing six-wicket victory over Lucknow Super Giants in the IPL 2024 match on Friday. With this win, DC achieved a milestone that no other team had previously accomplished.
title: DC create unique record against LSG

description: Australia's Jake Fraser-McGurk made a memorable IPL debut with a fiery half-century, while spinner Kuldeep Yadav sparkled with the ball as Delhi Capitals clinched a confidence-boosting six-wicket victory over Lucknow Super Giants. Ayush Badoni's unbeaten 55 off 35 balls powered the Super Giants to a respectable total of 167/7 after Kuldeep's impressive three-wicket haul of 3/20.
title: IPL: Fraser-McGurk, Kuldeep guide DC to six-wicket win over LSG

description: The young Australian cricketer, who scored a quickfire 55 off 35 balls with the help of 2 fours and 5 sixes, made short work of LSG's left-arm spinner Krunal Pandya, hitting him for three consecutive sixes. DC finally registered their second win of the season, beating hosts LSG by six wickets, riding on debutant Fraser-McGurk's fine half century and skipper Rishabh Pant's 24-ball 41, which included 4 fours and 2 sixes.
title: Watch: Fraser-McGurk hits hat-trick of sixes, slams fifty on IPL debut

description: Residents reported heavy Israeli fire in central Gaza on Friday, with regional tensions soaring after Iran threatened reprisals over a strike in Syria this month that killed two Iranian generals. Authorities in the Hamas-ruled territory reported dozens of new air strikes in Gaza's central region.
title: Israel pounds Gaza as Iran attack threat puts region on edge

description: The defense ministry has issued a tender to Hindustan Aeronautics Limited (HAL) for the purchase of 97 LCA Mark 1A fighter jets, valued at over Rs 65,000 crore. This marks the Indian government's largest order for domestically manufactured military equipment. Recently dispatched by the defense ministry to HAL, the tender grants a three-month period for a response.
title: Mega order: Defence ministry to buy 97 LCA Mark 1As from HAL

description: Pakistan's economic outlook remains uncertain due to political instability and supply chain disruptions. Growth is forecasted to gradually improve, supported by various factors including currency depreciation, inflation projection, and IMF support for reform agenda.
title: Pakistan's economic outlook 'uncertain', says ADB

description: BJP dropped Maharashtra CM Eknath Shinde and Deputy CM Ajit Pawar from its roster of star campaigners in the state. A revised list of 40 star campaigners, headed by Prime Minister Narendra Modi, was presented to the Election Commission of India by the party. The NCP (SCP) faction had filed a complaint with the ECI accusing the BJP of breaching the Representation of the People Act and electoral code by featuring names of politicians from other parties as its star campaigners.
title: BJP drops CM Shinde, Dy CM Pawar from list of star campaigners

description: MS Dhoni's popularity remains as strong as ever, even without his role as Chennai Super Kings skipper. In fact, his fan base is reaching new heights, showcasing his enduring appeal among enthusiasts.
title: Dhoni is still the crowd's favourite. Here's why

description: The moment this iconic picture surfaced on social media, the internet was abuzz with speculation. However, based on its appearance, the image most likely depicts an advertising shoot in a restaurant. These kinds of ad shoots are quite common to maintain the glam quotient of the glitzy Indian Premier League (IPL) away from the on-field action.
title: Viral pic of Dhoni, Sachin, Rohit in one frame breaks internet
Khalistan Zindabad Force member arrested from Delhi airport

description: P-TAL brand, post-Shark Tank India Season 3, thanked investors Aman Gupta, Namita Thapar, Anupam Mittal, Vineeta Singh, Amit Jain. Artisans showed gratitude with cheques. Fans praised the innovative reels shared by the brand.
title: Shark Tank's pitchers return cheques to sharks with blessings

description: Women and children in Pakistan's religious minority communities are vulnerable to forced religious conversion and marriage, as well as sexual assault and trafficking, UN experts said on Thursday. The statement also urged Pakistani authorities to treat all women, including those from the "Hindu and Christian" communities, equally.
title: UN experts condemn forced marriages of minorities in Pak

description: Force Motors teases the debut of the 5-door Gurkha model in India, showcasing potential upgrades in design and interiors to intensify competition in the off-road SUV segment.
title: Force Gurkha 5-door teaser reveals fresh details

description: The Ministry of External Affairs (MEA) on Friday said the deaths of Indian students in the United States, and are "multicausal" and investigations in the recent cases are underway, with Indian authorities taking up the issue with concerned authorities in the US. Addressing a weekly press briefing ​​​the MEA spokesperson highlighted the unfortunate incidents involving Indian-origin students in the US.
title: What MEA said on deaths of Indian students in US

description: In T20 cricket, there's constant pressure to maintain a high run rate, which can sometimes lead to batsmen playing aggressive shots even in the early stages of their innings. Explaining the challenges of T20s, West Indian Nicholas Pooran, representing Lucknow Super Giants in the IPL 2024, stated that it is all about execution in different situations and that the key to success is hard work.
title: 'The key to power hitting is...': Pooran on the challenges of batting in T20s
'Smriti Irani's choice of words shows mental bankruptcy'

description: In the dynamic entertainment sphere, each day unfolds with a myriad of captivating tales. From Shahid Kapoor's touching family video to the shelving of 'Sardarni,' featuring Priyanka Chopra and Diljit Dosanjh, and Arbaaz Khan and Sshura Khan's joyous Eid celebration after marriage, here are today's top five stories. Additionally, Alia Bhatt's role as a mediator between Ranbir Kapoor and Salman Khan and veteran actor Sayaji Shinde's hospitalization due to chest pain have garnered attention and concern.
title: Arbaaz-Shhura's first eid, Alia turning peacemaker: Top 5 news
Fresh violence erupts in Manipur, one left injured
'Talk about real issues': RJD's Tejashwi on PM Modi's mutton remark

description: Earlier this month, RBI governor Shaktikanta Das in his monetary policy statement said, “Inflation has come down significantly but remains above the 4 per cent target. Food inflation continues to exhibit considerable volatility impeding the ongoing disinflation process.”
title: March CPI inflation eases to 4.85% in March

description: In the current season, Mohammed Siraj has managed to secure only four wickets in six matches, significantly below his performance standard. His average and economy rate have also suffered, standing at 57.25 and 10.40 respectively. This is a stark contrast to his impressive showing in the IPL 2023, where he secured 10 wickets with an economy rate of 5.9 in the Powerplay overs.
title: 'Siraj is a champion bowler but he needs...': Bhajji on pacer's poor form

description: China and India are making progress in resolving the border standoff, with close communication ongoing, according to a senior foreign ministry official. The official's comments were further elaboration on China's reaction to PM Modi's recent statement in which he said that for New Delhi, ties with Beijing are important and the "prolonged situation" at the borders should be addressed urgently.
title: China says 'great positive progress' made to resolve border row with India
WB PDS scam: ED attaches Rs 150 cr worth assets
'Do not go to Iran, Israel': MEA issues travel advisory

description: ZeroPe, led by Ashneer Grover and Delhi NBFC Mukut Finvest, offers up to Rs 5 lakhs instant medical loans. Third Unicorn, Grover's venture post BharatPe, prioritizes app development including CrickPe fantasy platform.
title: Ashneer Grover returns to fintech space with this new app

description: Spokesperson Randhir Jaiswal said that India is closely monitoring the situation. "We are closely monitoring the security situation in Myanmar, particularly in the Rakhine State. Necessary steps have been taken to ensure the safety of our citizens," he said at his weekly media briefing. "We have temporarily relocated our staff at CGI (Consulate General of India) Sittwe to Yangon. Our Consulate in Mandalay remains fully functional."
title: India relocates diplomatic staff in restive Myanmar

description: Renowned singer Ed Sheeran performed a song for Samaira, the daughter of India's cricket team captain, Rohit Sharma. Rohit had recently been featured on the well-known Indian program 'Breakfast with Champions,' sharing the stage with Ed Sheeran and host Gaurav Kapoor. During the episode, the trio delved into a dynamic discussion, ranging from cricket talk to exploring the music industry. Ritika, Rohit's wife, and their daughter Samaira were also present, adding to the lively atmosphere.
title: Watch: Rohit Sharma picks song for daughter; Ed Sheeran sings

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi defended the Constitution's sanctity and India's national security during a rally in Barmer. He criticized the opposition for undermining the Constitution and aligning with anti-national forces. Modi emphasized the BJP's commitment to inclusive growth and highlighted contrasting visions for India's future.
title: 'Not even Ambedkar ...': PM takes on oppn's Constitution remarks

description: Virat Kohli garnered acclaim for his gesture of stepping forward to back Hardik Pandya, urging the crowd to applaud the Mumbai Indians skipper instead of expressing disapproval through boos.
title: Harbhajan, Sehwag praise Kohli's sportsmanship

description: P-TAL, known for crafting brass, copper, and kansa products, made history on Shark Tank India by securing investments from all five investors. The company returned symbolic 'cheques' of Love, Respect, Blessings to express gratitude uniquely.
title: This startup is 'returning special cheques' to Shark Tank investors

description: Pompeii's recent excavation uncovered a banquet hall with mythological frescos, including Apollo's seduction of Cassandra and Helen of Troy meeting Paris. The well-preserved site also features a bakery and mosaic floor, offering insights into ancient Roman life.
title: Hidden for 2,000 yrs, striking paintings uncovered in Pompeii
2024 sees rise in US measles cases: All you need to know

description: Bharat Rasthra Samithi (BRS) leader K Kavitha has been placed in 3-day CBI custody for alleged involvement in the Delhi excise policy scam. Scheduled for court appearance on April 15, the decision was made by Special Judge Kaveri Baweja after hearing arguments of the Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) as well as Kavitha's counsel.​​
title: K Kavitha sent to 3-day CBI custody till April 15

description: Amid escalating tensions in the Middle East, Russia, Germany, and Britain have called for restraint among regional actors as the possibility of an Iranian retaliatory strike against Israel grows. The calls for calm come in response to the recent airstrike on April 1 that targeted an Iranian embassy compound in Damascus, killing a top Iranian general and six military officers. Iran has vowed vengeance for the attack, which it attributes to Israel.
title: How Iran is stoking a 'psychological terror' in Israel

description: Google is discontinuing its VPN by Google One service due to low usage. Users in India need not worry as the service was not available there. Existing users will switch to third-party VPN options, while older Pixel models will transition to a built-in service.
title: Why Indian users need not worry about Google shutting VPN service

description: Omega Seiki Mobility and Exponent Energy introduce the OSM Stream City Qik electric three-wheeler priced at Rs 3.25 lakh. It offers rapid charging, 126 km ARAI certified range, 533 km payload, and plans for charging station expansions in various cities.
title: OSM Stream City Qik launched at Rs 3.25 lakh

description: Located about 637 light-years away, WASP-76 b was initially discovered in 2013 through the Wide Angle Search for Planets project. This planet, which orbits very close to its star—about 20 times closer than Mercury orbits the sun—completes an orbit in just 1.8 days. It is noted for its extreme conditions, including a "day side" that reaches temperatures around 4,350 degrees Fahrenheit due to its permanent exposure to the star, a Live Science report said.
title: 'Rainbow glory': Strange light spotted over distant 'hell planet'

description: UK expedites 'DragonFire' laser system deployment on Royal Navy warships to counter Russian threats, showcasing military technology innovation and cost-effective defense solutions for evolving security challenges.
title: UK rushes to deploy laser 'death ray' amid Russian threats
The uncontrolled, Delhi Rent Control Act, 1958

description: TCS Q4 results: The company reported a revenue of Rs 61,237 crore, which is a 3.5% year-on-year growth. According to the TCS press release, the growth was led by India (+37.9%), UK (+6.2%), and Manufacturing (+9.7%).
title: TCS Q4 results: Tata Consultancy Services reports PAT of Rs 12,434cr

description: Rouse Avenue Court instructed ED and CBI to respond to Manish Sisodia's bail plea regarding excise policy irregularities by April 20, with allegations of favors, diverted gains, and slow trial proceedings. ​​Sisodia was arrested by CBI on February 26 and ED on March 9 last year in connection with these allegations. He resigned from the Delhi cabinet on February 28, 2023.
title: Manish Sisodia interim bail: Court issues notice to ED, CBI

description: Mary Kom steps down as India's chef-de-mission for Paris Olympics due to personal reasons, as announced by IOA. Her decision was respected by PT Usha, who will soon announce a replacement. Kom will continue to support the athletes. Her appointment was first announced by the IOA on March 21. Usha said she had a conversation with Mary Kom after receiving her letter.
title: 'Embarassing ... but no choice': Mary Kom steps down as Paris Olympics Chef-de-Mission

description: Blinkit teams up with Lenskart to provide fast delivery of various products, including sunglasses, computer glasses, and the Hustlr range. Founder Albinder Dhindsa shared the collaborations on social media, ensuring quick access to items like PlayStation 5.
title: Blinkit has '10-min' solution to your specs 'troubles and needs'
Cafe blast arrest: Mamata hits back at BJP's 'safe haven' barb

description: Bryan Johnson's social media post on aging sparked criticism. Despite backlash, he invests in health regimes. Johnson, a Silicon Valley figure, faces debates on ethics in his anti-aging journey toward eternal youth.
title: US tech entrepreneur's anti-ageing photo sparks debate

description: Kolkata Metro introduces 'Tom and Jerry' on digital screens, delighting passengers. The initiative aims to enhance travel experience with wholesome entertainment. Positive user reactions and demands for similar initiatives highlight the universal appeal of the show.
title: Kolkata Metro starts screening Tom and Jerry inside trains

description: Harbhajan Singh has praised Mumbai Indians batter Suryakumar Yadav, comparing him to South African legend AB de Villiers for their effortless batting style. Yadav's stellar performance led Mumbai Indians to victory against Royal Challengers Bengaluru, and Singh expressed relief that he no longer has to face such daunting batting displays.

PM Modi's 'mughal mentality' dig at Rahul Gandhi & Lalu Yadav

description: On Thursday, Prince William made his first public appearance since his wife, Kate Middleton, confirmed her cancer diagnosis. for Thursday night, the 41-year-old was photographed at a football match with his 10-year-old son George, cheering for his team, Aston Villa. Kate, through a video released last month, had revealed that she had cancer diagnosis and was undergoing 'preventative chemotherapy.'
title: Prince William makes 1st appearance since wife's cancer news

description: Five major steel companies, including Tata Steel and SAIL, secured contracts worth Rs 1,586.39 crore from Indian Railways. SAIL emerged as the top beneficiary, securing a significant portion of both tenders. Tata Steel follows closely with a contract to supply 52,753 MT of steel.
title: Indian Railways awards big steel procurement orders for Rs 1,586 cr

description: Incidents of contamination in college canteens, like dead ants in samosas at Dyal Singh College, and unhygienic practices at OP Jindal Global University, highlight the need for food safety scrutiny in educational institutions.
title: Dead ants in samosas: 'Bear Grylls bhi to kha leta hai'

description: Mumbai Indians wicketkeeper-batsman Ishan Kishan has shifted his focus from securing a spot in India's T20 World Cup squad to individual improvement and team progress in the IPL 2024. Kishan, who recently took a hiatus from cricket, emphasized that the World Cup is not in his hands and is taking things one match at a time.
title: 'It is not in my hands...': Ishan Kishan on T20 WC aspirations

description: Amazon CEO Andy Jassy criticizes regulators for blocking mergers, impacting iRobot's acquisition. Jassy highlights challenges with Chinese companies and competition from Anker, Ecovacs, Roborock, and SharkNinja.
title: Amazon CEO finds 'big Chinese problem' in blocking iRobot deal

description: Karnataka BJP criticizes Siddaramaiah-led government after NIA arrests two in Rameshwaram blast. Accused termed 'Brothers of Congress'. Allegations of promoting terror policies, ISIS presence, turning Karnataka into a terror hub.
title: Bengaluru cafe bomber arrested: 'IS has set up shop in Karnataka'

description: Antique Stock Broking anticipates a 15-17% telecom tariff hike post Lok Sabha elections, with Airtel's ARPU potentially reaching Rs 286 by FY27. Jio is noted for gaining market share amidst high competitive intensity.
title: Airtel may increase mobile tariff by 15-17% post LS polls: Report
Tamil Nadu to pull out all stops to attract Elon Musk

description: Gopichand Thotakura is set to make history as the first Indian to embark on a journey into space as a tourist. Thotakura will join a six-person crew aboard Blue Origin's New Shepard mission, embarking on a journey that will take them beyond the Earth's atmosphere. His experience spans commercial jet piloting, bush flying, aerobatics, seaplane, glider, and hot air balloon piloting.
title: Meet Gopi Thotakura: First Indian to journey into space as a tourist

description: India is examining its trade agreement with Asean to rectify discrepancies hindering domestic manufacturing. The review focuses on import duties, rules of origin, and non-tariff barriers to address an inverted duty structure.  Concerns arise over the rising trade deficit with Asean.
title: How India is working with Asean to spur domestic manufacturing

description: Rohit Sharma has expressed his dedication to the sport and aspiration to secure a World Cup victory for India. He has dismissed retirement plans and is still playing well. His ultimate goal is to win the World Cup with India, with a WTC final in 2025, underscoring his commitment to achieving significant milestones in international cricket.
title: 'Really want to win WC…': Rohit dismisses retirement plans

description: Meta is testing Meta AI chatbot on WhatsApp in India, expanding from US trials. The chatbot integrates suggestions for user interaction through the search interface, ensuring user privacy. It also allows users to search within conversations easily.
title: WhatsApp starts testing Meta AI chatbot in India: What it does

description: The Shahs' political fortunes are tied to the Badrinath temple, affecting election outcomes. Despite historical defeats, Mala Rajya Laxmi Shah won in 2019. With upcoming polls on April 19 and temple reopening on May 12, will luck favor them again?
title: Why Badrinath portals closing matters in this LS seat

description: Former spinner Harbhajan Singh praised Indian pace sensation Jasprit Bumrah for his exceptional performance in the IPL and his relentless quest for improvement. Singh praised Mumbai Indians strike bowler's ability to learn from day one and continuously improve, even after a five-wicket haul against Royal Challengers Bengaluru at the Wankhede stadium.

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi assured a peaceful Lok Sabha election in Jammu and Kashmir, highlighting improved security conditions and the fulfillment of promises to the region's residents. He challenged the opposition to reinstate Article 370. The rally in Udhampur supported Union minister Jitendra Singh's re-election bid.

title: Gold prices cross Rs 72,000/10g mark; silver high at Rs 84,000/kg

description: Hussey, the ex-Australian batsman, has the experience of not only playing under Dhoni's leadership at CSK but also as the current batting coach of the five-time IPL champions. Talking to Hussey, Ashwin, a former CSK player himself, sought the Australian's insights into Dhoni's methods for nurturing champion players and building victorious teams.
title: 'Dhoni not just looks for good players but also good people'

description: Vikrant Massey credits director Rajkumar Hirani for recommending him to Vidhu Vinod Chopra for "12th Fail," leading to his acclaimed performance and the film's success. Massey expresses gratitude to Hirani for his continuous support and humility. They are rumoured to be  collaborating on a web show, with Hirani producing and his assistant directing.
title: I thank Rajkumar Hirani for 12th Fail every time I meet him: Massey

description: The UK government plans to introduce a new tax regime in April 2025 affecting NRIs and recent migrants. This change will end the tax exemption for non-doms, imposing taxes on worldwide income after four years of residency. Tax experts are advising on financial planning strategies amidst concerns over UK's tax appeal.
title: New proposed tax regime may make UK less attractive to migrate

description: Delhi witnesses frequent fights, especially in public transport, often going viral on social media. A recent incident near Madhuban Chowk involved a bus conductor and a car driver. The police officer suggested calling 100 for help, sparking online confusion and hilarity.
title: Delhi's viral fight video: Car driver, DTC conductor beat each other

description: A tragic accident in New Delhi involving a bus carrying school children resulted in one fatality and injuries to five individuals, including three school children.
